being caribou is a 2005 documentary film that chronicles the travels of husband and wife &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and leanne allison following the migration of the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; caribou herd , in order to explore the arctic refuge drilling controversy . the journey lasted 5 months , starting from the community of old crow , yukon on april 8 , 2003 and ending september 8 . the film is produced by the national film board of canada .